[The primary infection in the Heddon pigs has not been revealed, if it is
known. The virus didn't jump from Asia to the UK all by itself. Granted
these were swill-fed pigs, but that merely points the finger at one more
possible source in those kitchens producing swill as a side-product of
English meals. If they were using ham or sausages contaminated with
possible virus, those animals would have been infected, perhaps, within the
past 3 months in whatever region the ham or sausage meat came from. - Mod.TG
